Introduction
Are you Router and Switcher Network Engineer, looking for a lucrative consulting working for a Top 10 Fortune 500 Oil and Gas Company? Brunel Energy has a position available for a hands on Network Maintenance Specialist looking for more autonomy and independence at work, as the go-to IT person in a smaller department. If interested send me your Resume today!
Description
Seeking 2 highly qualified IT Network Engineers to assist in the migration of all external connections from legacy Extranet Environments to their recently built next generation Extranet Infrastructure. Candidates must have experience implementing large complex network solutions based on designs and specifications provided by the Network Design Team. In depth knowledge of IP networks based on multi-vendor environments is required including Cisco, Juniper, Palo Alto, Big Switch and others.
Position Responsibilities:
Works with teams to provide advanced design, architecture and diagnostic support;
Responsible for the design, configuration, development, integration, implementation of network solutions;
Combines a good understanding of IT with a considerable knowledge of industry, business function, or service offering in the engagement.
Top Required Skills:
Minimum 5+ years of Data Center Experience;
Large Enterprise Level Experience required, preferably Oil/Gas experience;
Hands-on experience and a thorough understanding of routing protocols specifically BGP, ISIS, OSPF and EIGRP;
In depth knowledge of IP networks based on multi-vendor environments is required including Cisco (routing and switching platforms + NEXUS), Juniper (MX platform), Big Switch and others;
Must be able to work and collaborate with multiple work groups.
Preferred Skill Set:
Bachelor’s Degree (computer science, technical engineer, telecommunications) preferred, military experience or equivalent experience;
CCIE /CCNP certification strongly preferred;
Previous Cloud Integration experience;
Automation and scripting (software defined networking);
Previous experience working for a refinery or Oil and Gas company.
Additional skills (highly recommended):
In depth knowledge of VPN technologies;
Experience working with carrier class MPLS services;
Experience working with private MPLS;
Experience in the implementation of Internet Peering;
Experience implementing a variety of Layer 2 and Layer 3 carrier based Ethernet services;
Ability to design and implement complex IP schemas for both IPV4 and IPV6;
Be able to communicate specifications and requirements to stakeholders;
Ability to provided top class technical documentation - PLUS;
Experience with BMC’s Remedy IT Service Management Suite - PLUS;
Have the ability to trouble shoot extremely complex network problems;
Excellent interpersonal skills.
What We Offer
Brunel Energy provides specialist personnel to the international oil & gas, petrochemical, power generation and construction industries. Our clients are predominantly major operating companies and international engineering or construction companies. Through a network of 40 offices in 5 continents (Europe, Americas, Asia, Africa and Australia) we currently second over 8,000 Technical Engineering Specialists to the largest multinational Oil & Gas Companies and major EPC Contractors, through well-established global supply agreements.
Compensation:
Contract Hire
Full Time + benefits
Competitive wages and benefit package
Our client is one of the world's leading integrated Energy companies. This top 10 Fortune 500 Corporation has pioneered everything from upstream exploration and production, midstream transportation, power and trading, to downstream manufacturing and retail.

 Job Description
Genesis10 is seeking a Network Engineer for our client, a leading telecommunications company located in Jonesboro, AR. This is a direct-hire opportunity.
Job Summary
The Network Engineer is responsible for technology evaluation, equipment standardization, documentation, network architecture, and service development related to the Client's network. The role has a general understanding of all services offered by the company, with an emphasis in layer 2 and 3 services.
Job Description:
Generates quote requests, orders, and negotiates directly with vendors;
Prepares project budgets and manages capital and operating expenses on engineering projects; provide regular reporting and forecasting related to project budgets;
Attends various meetings with management, departments and vendors to ensure company objectives are met;
Participates in inter-departmental planning meetings to coordinate and communicate activities related to the successful completion of projects;
Works closely with the Operational and planning teams network deployments;
Works closely with other engineering teams, network and field technicians, product development and OSS teams to design and roll out new data infrastructure, technologies and services;
Works closely with Product Marketing to ensure successful delivery of all technical components of new services and service enhancements;
Works closely with Operational and Engineering teams to develop provisioning guides, deployment guides, and training packages to ensure new technologies and services are supportable by the operations group;
Configures and commissions network elements;
Runs technology and service trials;
Travels to project sites and job areas as required;
Perform and analyze packet captures;
Performs other duties as assigned by Network and Service Architecture Manager
Required Experience and Skills:
Knowledge of modern service provider data networks, technologies and protocols;
Knowledge of SD-WAN architecture and ability to integrate it into service delivery types and network topologies.
Knowledge of access technologies; such as G-PON, XGS-PON, xDSL, G.Fast, FTTH
Knowledge of network system design, development methods, and techniques;
Knowledge of network management practices and procedures;
Knowledge and the ability to design in all of the OSI layers model;
Knowledge of IPv6 routing protocols and best practices;
Evaluates and standardize IP technologies and architectures in relation to the infrastructure and service needs of the Client in a Service Provider Network;
Develops policies and standards for protocols and technologies such as BGP, IS-IS, OSPFv3, MPLS, Segment Routing, Multicast protocols; SIP, and MGCP;
Must have a deep understanding of QOS within the OSI layers;
Skill in operating various office equipment such as personal computer, various software programs including Microsoft Office applications (Excel, Outlook, Visio);
Skill in problem identification and resolution;
Skill in oral and written communication;
Skill in reading and interpreting technical documents such as vendor deployment guidelines, white papers and configuration manuals;
Ability to communicate with customers, employees, and various business contacts in a professional and courteous manner;
Ability to organize and prioritize multiple work assignments;
Ability to pay close attention to detail;
Ability to work independently;
Ability to make sound decisions using information at hand;
Ability to work in a team environment
Education:
Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Networking, or a related field plus three years of telecommunications technical experience or an equivalent combination of education and experience preferred.
If you have the described qualifications and are interested in this exciting opportunity, apply today!
About Genesis10:
Genesis10 is a leading U.S. business and technology consulting firm with hundreds of clients needing proven talent and solutions to power their strategic initiatives. If you are a high performing business or IT professional with solid, referenced experience, we want to meet you. Genesis10 recruiters and delivery professionals are highly accomplished career advocates, who get to know you beyond your resume to position you with the opportunities that fit your skills, experience and aspirations. We have benefit options to fit your needs and a support staff that works with you from placement throughout your engagement – project after project. To learn more about Genesis10 and to view all our available career opportunities, please visit us at www.genesis10.com.
"Genesis10 is an Equal Opportunity Employer, M/F/D/V”
