JOB DESCRIPTION
Scope of Work
The Network Engineer is responsible for the implementation, maintenance, development and support to Senior Network Engineer in design of communication networks and connectivity components within the organization and/or project facilities. The goal of the Network Engineer is to ensure maximum performance of a high traffic network infrastructure while maintaining the system integrity. (S)he should deeply understand the logical and physical, private and public network components including WAPs, firewalls, routers, switches, controllers, transit, peering, transport, cloud and security protocols and techniques. Primary duties include establishment and maintenance of networks by building net configurations and connections, maintenance and protection of data, hardware and software from different attacks, troubleshooting network problems and equipment, carrying out disaster recovery operations and replacing faulty network hardware components when necessary.
Duties and Responsibilities
Assist in design and development of the network infrastructure including networking software, computer hardware and other;
Establish network environment through defined, documented and enforced system standards;
Perform modelling, analysis and installation of integrated network;
Program and configure routers, switches and other equipment;
Configure DNS servers;
Configure hosted IP voice services;
Monitor network availability, performance and utilization;
Troubleshoot, diagnose and resolve problems and outages;
Maintain and troubleshoot:
LAN, WLAN, WAN;
Firewall landscape;
Core and next generation network services (DNS, DHCP, access control; IDS, IPS, proxies, ATP, DLP, SD-WAN, etc.);
VMware, Checkpoint and Microsoft virtualization technologies;
VPN remote access solution;
Maintain, configure and monitor virus protection software;
Perform disaster recovery operations and data backups when required;
Replace faulty network hardware components when required;
Coordinate, evolve and implement network security techniques and monitor access;
Configure and maintain firewall and manage security related to hacking;
Design and implement new solutions to improve the resilience of current network environment;
Assess live traffic patterns to optimize network capacity planning;
Schedule and perform updates and upgrades to the latest releases;
Report network operational status by managing projects and prioritizing information;
Manage owned domain names and coordinate network access and use;
Manage and audit IP addressing and hosted devices within data centres;
Perform network operations across multiple on-prem and cloud sites;
Remotely monitor and manage system alerts, troubleshoot and find faults;
Provide technical support;
Assist in preparation of all related network documentation.
Essential Requirements and Qualifications
At least Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related field;
5+ years of relevant work experience in network administration and maintenance;
Understanding the network infrastructure and hardware and knowledge of relevant protocols;
Knowledge of the local area network (LAN), wireless local area network (WLAN) and wide area network (WAN - MPLS, VPLS, VPN);
Proficiency in management and troubleshooting of the network infrastructure devices (access points, firewall, routers, switches, controllers);
Proficiency in switching (Capacity Planning & VLAN’s), routing (OSPF, RIPv2, BGP) and IP addressing;
Quality of Service (QoS) and rate shaping;
Checkpoint: CSSA/CSSP;
Understanding of VPNs, POTS, VOIP, SIP Trunking, BGP, VLAN, Large Scale Wi-Fi Deployments;
Understanding of OSI or related models;
Proficiency with fiber-based PON LAN networks;
Understanding of public cloud platforms (Microsoft Azure and AWS);
Experience in network security, encryption and security concepts (DDoS protection, intrusion prevention and detection systems (IPS/IDS) and proxy servers);
Security software (anti-virus, anti-SPAM, anti-Spyware and other);
Virtual Private Network (VPN) and encryption/tunneling protocols;
Ability to prepare documentation for design and planning network communication systems;
Ability to learn quickly using trainings, documentation and internet resources;
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills and ability to perform well under pressure;
Ability to work on call outside of regular working hours;
Working well both independently and in team;
Excellent communication skills.
Desirable Qualifications
Understanding of other networks such as MANs, GANs, SAN, CAN, PAN, DAN;
Additional certifications such as Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) or Cisco Certified Network Professional (CCNP), Microsoft Certified Solutions Expert (MCSE) or Microsoft Certified Solutions Associate (MCSA), CompTIA Network+, etc.;
Proficiency managing and configuring network monitoring tools;
Networking certification (JNCIE/CCNA/CCNP/CCIE);
Firewall certification (CCSA/CCSM/CSSA);
Cloud certification (CSSP);
Ability to multitask;
Desire to learn, apply learnings and willingness to teach others.

